@title Elang API to CouchDb 
@doc
eCouch is an <a href="http://www.erlang.org/">Erlang</a> application that provides access to <a href="http://couchdb.org/"> CouchDb</a> servers.

It uses the <a href="http://www.lshift.net/blog/2007/02/17/json-and-json-rpc-for-erlang">rfc4627</a> module from <a href="http://www.lshift.net/">LShift</a>
The design was inspired in the article <a href="http://www.trapexit.org/Building_a_Non-blocking_TCP_server_using_OTP_principles">Building a Non-blocking TCP server using OTP principles</a> and assumes that <a href="http://www.erlang.org/doc/apps/inets/index.html">inets</a> application is running.
